    h4 Open-source work
    markdown:
      Most of my projects are on Github, but they are split between [github.com/nathanaeljones](http://github.com/nathanaeljones) and [github.com/imazen](http://github.com/imazen).


    h4 StudioJS
    a href="https://github.com/nathanaeljones/studiojs" A jQuery-based image editor
    h4 libwebp for .NET
    a href="https://github.com/imazen/libwebp-net"  libwebp 0.2.0 lacked a .NET wrapper, so I made one - with full P/Invoke coverage.
    h5 lightresize
    a href="https://github.com/imazen/lightresize" lightresize is an embeddable .NET class for primitive image resizing which doesn't depend on System.Web - but also lacks 95% of ImageResizer functionality.
    h5 CropImage.NET
    a href="https://github.com/nathanaeljones/cropimage"  After the (very) popular WebCropImage project was abandoned and deleted, I resurrected the project and gave it some much-needed love.
    h5 WebFormsFixes
    a href="https://github.com/nathanaeljones/WebFormsFixes" Some utilites to make WebForms a bit more bearable.
    h5 HardwiredCMS
    a href="http://hardwiredcms.com"  After 2 years of Nesta, I got tired of leaky abstractions, and decided to simplify things.
    h5 Nesta
    markdown:
      Nesta is one of the best micro-CMSes, and I've contributed a lot to the project. I [added format extensibility to core](https://github.com/nathanaeljones/nesta) (not yet merged) and created [nesta-plugin-tags](https://github.com/nathanaeljones/nesta-plugin-tags), [nesta-plugin-simplicity](https://github.com/nathanaeljones/nesta-plugin-simplicity), [nesta-plugin-wordpress](https://github.com/nathanaeljones/nesta-plugin-wordpress), and [nesta-plugin-aliases](https://github.com/nathanaeljones/nesta-plugin-aliases)
    h5 WeaverEngine
